eNCA's Siphamandla Goge has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Treasurer General Paul Mashatile says party unity is crucial for the survival of the liberation movement. Mashatile was addressing delegates at the governing party's Limpopo elective conference in Polokwane. Stan Mathabatha is seeking a third term as the party's provincial chairperson. READ: Ekurhuleni ANC elective conference begins after delays He is up against Public Works MEC, Dickson Masemola. Mashatile urged delegates to emerge united from the 3-day conference. "Comrades as we sit in this conference, we must remember that this is a year of unity and renewal," he said. "This conference must place greater emphasis on unity and renewal of our movement."